ious | 1994 | Due to the game's complexity, a visual demo is prepared,<ref name="Mashable Inside" /> and screenshots of the game are displayed on a floor-to-ceiling, multi-column [[mural]].<ref name="PCMag" /> | 1 | <ref name="two" /><ref name="three" /> |- !scope="row"| ''[[The Sims (video game)|The Sims]]'' | [[Maxis]] | Various | 2000 | Available only as a video demonstration<ref name="New York Times" /> | 1 | <ref name="two" /><ref name="three" /> |- !scope="row"| ''[[Snake (video game)|Snake]]'' | [[Nokia]] | Various | 1997 | | 4 | |- !scope="row"| ''[[Space Invaders]]'' | [[Taito]] | [[Arcade game|Arcade]] | 1978 | | 2 | <ref name="four" /> |- !scope="row"| ''[[Street Fighter II: The World Warrior|Street Fighter II]]'' | [[Capcom]] | [[Arcade game|Arcade]] | 1991 | | 3 | |- !scope="row"| ''[[Tempest (video game)|Tempest]]'' | [[Atari, Inc.|Atari]] | [[Arcade game|Arcade]] | 1981 | | 2 | <ref name="four" /> |- !scope="row"| ''[[Tetris]]'' | {{sortname|Alexey|Pajitnov}} | Various | 1984 | MoMA's copy of ''Tetris'' runs on an [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] computer mimicking the specific [[History of the Soviet Union (1982–91)|Soviet-era]] computer it was designed for in 1984.<ref name="Dwarf Fortress" /> | 1 | <ref name="two" /><ref name="three" /> |- !scope="row"| ''[[Vib-Ribbon]]'' | [[NanaOn-Sha]] | [[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]] | 1999 | | 1 | <ref name="two" /><ref name="three" /> |- !scope="row"| ''[[Yars' Revenge]]'' | [[Atari, Inc.|Atari]] | [[Atari 2600]] | 1982 | | 2 | <ref name="four" /> |}
