{{Infobox organization | name = Northern Colorado Writers Workshop | native_name = | native_name_lang = | named_after = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | logo = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | map2 = | map2_size = | map2_alt = | map2_caption = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = | merged = | successor = | formation = 1972 | founder = Edward Bryant | founding_location = | extinction = <!-- use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merger = | type = Invitation-only, non-profit writing workshop | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = | purpose = | headquarters = | location = | coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline, title}} --> | region = | services = | products = | methods = | fields = | membership = Professional and near-professional writers | membership_year = | language = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = | leader_name = | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = | parent_organization = | subsidiaries = | secessions = | affiliations = | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | disbursements = | expenses = | expenses_year = | endowment = | staff = | staff_year = | volunteers = | volunteers_year = | slogan = | mission = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | remarks = | formerly = | footnotes = }}
The '''Northern Colorado Writers Workshop''' is an invitation-only, non-profit writing workshop founded in 1972 by [[Edward Bryant]]. The writing genres of its members include mainly [[science fiction]], [[fantasy]], [[horror fiction|horror]], and [[mystery fiction|mystery]].<ref>[https://essaychip.com Professional Writers Workshop]</ref> Membership in the workshop is generally limited to professional and near-professional writers, and includes a number of [[Hugo award|Hugo]], [[Nebula award|Nebula]], [[Bram Stoker Award|Bram Stoker]], [[International Horror Guild Award|International Horror Guild]], and [[World Fantasy Award]] winners.
